Great — now that it's all set up, here’s exactly what you need to do from now on to:

---

### ✅ 1. Save Your Work (Push to GitHub)

Whenever you make changes to your project files:

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "your meaningful message here"
git push origin main
```

This saves your work to GitHub (just like Google Drive for code).

---

### 🚀 2. Deploy to GitHub Pages

After pushing, or anytime you want to update the live website:

```bash
npm run deploy
```

This rebuilds your project and publishes it to:
🔗 [https://sidwah.github.io/mYPortfolio](https://sidwah.github.io/mYPortfolio)

---

### 📝 Quick Summary of Workflow:

| Action                 | Command                        |
| ---------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| Track changes          | `git add .`                    |
| Save changes locally   | `git commit -m "your message"` |
| Push changes to GitHub | `git push origin main`         |
| Deploy to GitHub Pages | `npm run deploy`               |

You’re now in full control. Let me know when you want to add routing, pages, or animations!
